reviews.review_text:
Outstanding Althea One of the better Althea's--it just goes on and on.  If you need a ten-minute checkout at work: this is it.  The rest have their moments but the Althea is a standout!  Good sound overall.

James

Saw it on TV In a flat in West End London after a day in Hamstead Heath Pk.

This was my first live tape as my buddy Andy taped it.  In the UK the picture cut out somewhere during the first set but I listened to BBC to hear the whole thing including Pete Townshend(The Who opened and played a killer set).

This is a very good show from '81 and not a bad FM feed.  

A monster Shakedown happens only half way through the first set.  It's that kind of show.  They get a little tired in the latter half (they came on around eleven) of the second set but Pete re-invigorates them.  Nice Wharf Rat too.  Superb He's Gone>Other One.

Oh and a Sugaree for the ages.

And the fella below is right about Althea.  I think it's the best one I've ever heard.

feelin it This is one of my favorite shows. Garcia really means business on this one and he takes no prisoners! The second set "features" a Pete Townshend sit-in where he flails about aimlessly and generally makes a fool of himself. Luckily the Dead hold it together despite that distraction.
